      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(minimax): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nBound MiniMax OAuth HTTP response read using the shared provider JSON reader\nto prevent unbounded buffering from untrusted upstream JSON bodies.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/minimax/oauth.ts`: Replace `response.json()` with\n  `readProviderJsonResponse(response, minimax.oauth-code)` (shared 16 MiB default cap).\n  Video-generation provider intentionally unchanged — left for focused video PR #96889.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof: bounded reader cancels oversized stream\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_minimax_bound.mts\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Unit tests\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/oauth.test.ts\n Tests  12 passed (12)\n```\n\n_AI-assisted._",
